{"id":23554,"title":"Primary purulent pericarditis and secondary endocarditis: a case report.","abstract":"Purulent pericarditis is a rare diagnosis to be made. It is exceedingly rare as a primary infection. We describe the case of an 18-month-old boy who presented with primary purulent pericarditis and developed a secondary endocarditis. Current literature on the subject is reviewed and discussed. ","date":"2014-04-23","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24480459","annotations":[{"name":"Literature","weight":0.0366575,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Literature"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Endocarditis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endocarditis"},{"name":"Pericarditis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pericarditis"},{"name":"Pus","weight":0.0290048,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pus"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.0157616,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Case report","weight":0.0148276,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Case_report"},{"name":"Primary education","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primary_education"},{"name":"Secondary school","weight":0.0136738,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secondary_school"}]}
